I want to remind all of us that that same God is sovereign.

22:19.146 --> 22:24.536
His power, authority, and justice, no, no end and no, no bounds.

22:25.257 --> 22:27.742
His love is beyond compare.

22:28.323 --> 22:29.906
He is the king of king.

22:30.114 --> 22:34.281
the Lord of Lords, the Alpha Omega first and last beginning in the end.

22:34.381 --> 22:48.764
And that God, that very same God creator of the cosmos is looking at Israel in that story and saying, I know your wants and needs and desires and I have not forgotten you.

22:48.784 --> 22:50.066
That same God

22:50.210 --> 23:04.087
is looking at you right now with your finances, in your marriage, in your job, in this cultural moment, with all of your needs, wants and desires, and he's saying to you the same thing, I see you, I have not forgotten you.

23:08.532 --> 23:13.919
And he shares that promise, I know the plans I have for you.

23:15.901 --> 23:19.666
The healing, the justice, the restoration that we want,

23:19.778 --> 23:26.270
right now may not come how and when we want it, but it will come.

23:26.390 --> 23:28.093
That is the assurance we have in him.

23:28.133 --> 23:31.620
That is what he was trying to tell Israel, look, you messed up.

23:31.640 --> 23:33.764
There's a consequence, but that doesn't mean I've forgotten you.

23:33.804 --> 23:34.826
I haven't left you.

23:34.866 --> 23:38.452
So while you're here, this is how I want you to honor me.

23:38.493 --> 23:41.458
Be faithful and live in this way and trust me.

23:41.922 --> 23:44.885
Because it is coming, the rescue is coming.

23:45.045 --> 23:45.986
He says the same to us.

23:46.247 --> 23:55.076
You may not get the healing or the finances or the restoration or the things you want, exactly how you want it, when you want it, but I haven't forgotten you.

23:55.376 --> 23:56.838
It is coming.

23:57.238 --> 24:00.021
Remain faithful to me while you wait.

24:00.302 --> 24:02.224
In essence, it becomes a question of trust.

24:04.326 --> 24:11.794
God is looking at Israel and saying, will you trust me and remain faithful to me even while you're

24:11.874 --> 24:16.499
wants, needs, and desires, maybe aren't getting answered yet, and wait on me.

24:18.021 --> 24:32.536
He's looking at us and saying, I know your wants, needs, and desires, but while you wait on those, will you live faithfully, how I've called you to live, and will you trust me?

24:35.099 --> 24:41.586
He's given Israel, he's given us plenty of evidence that would warrant us trusting him,

24:41.762 --> 24:43.304
But doesn't mean that it's always easy.

24:44.125 --> 24:52.834
Friends, I have to tell you, when I prayed to God for this message, the first verse that he gave, he didn't, that where he first took me to was verse 13 of this chapter.

24:53.455 --> 24:57.499
You will seek me and find me when you seek me with all your heart.

24:58.521 --> 24:59.622
Oh, and that hits hard.

25:01.484 --> 25:02.565
Do you know why it's hard?

25:03.026 --> 25:04.687
You know why with all your heart is hard?

25:05.268 --> 25:07.090
Because I know exactly what that looks like.

25:07.970 --> 25:11.814
I am prone to give my heart and my all to many things.

25:11.834 --> 25:14.377
They just usually are senseless silly things.

25:15.218 --> 25:17.881
I can talk your ear off about soccer.

25:19.023 --> 25:23.027
I can talk your ear off about Star Wars and Lord of the Rings and geek stuff.

25:23.248 --> 25:25.030
It's one of the things Jim and I talk about the most.

25:27.833 --> 25:35.922
I will move heaven and earth to make sure that my schedule allows for me to spend countless hours watching the World Cup that's coming up this summer.

25:36.738 --> 25:44.432
or that new show, or another episode of that series, or whatever, to go on my hobbies, hiking and camping, whatever else.

25:45.013 --> 25:50.944
I know what it's like to spend the week living for a day and a moment and focus on my energy toward it.

25:51.526 --> 25:56.074
The hard thing is that all too often, that thing is not God.

25:59.360 --> 26:00.402
All too often,

26:00.642 --> 26:02.565
That thing is not time with him.

26:02.805 --> 26:03.967
It's not seeking him.

26:04.207 --> 26:05.529
It's not listening to him.

26:05.750 --> 26:08.013
And it's not doing what he calls me to do.

26:10.396 --> 26:12.339
I don't know if that sounds familiar to any of you.

26:13.982 --> 26:23.776
And then the hard thing becomes that when my wants, my needs and my desires rise to the surface, when I look at the news, when I look at the world around me and I say the prayer, Lord, change this.

26:24.037 --> 26:25.018
Lord, fix this.

26:25.739 --> 26:27.762
And I turn to God to discuss it.

26:29.218 --> 26:32.522
I find that I've wandered a bit off from God.

26:34.084 --> 26:47.800
Not denied my faith, not turned to a false God, but I just realized I'm not close to Him because I filled the space with other pursuits, other things, other distractions.

26:47.840 --> 26:53.647
And again, it doesn't have to be like outright downright sin, just other things.

26:54.268 --> 26:56.210
My heart has pursued

26:56.354 --> 27:00.439
other things more than God, and I've left Jesus to the side.

27:01.781 --> 27:08.910
But my knees, my ones, my desires, the crisis of life, too often what happens is I'm treating God like an emergency plan.

27:09.952 --> 27:11.754
In case of emergency, break Jesus.

27:11.954 --> 27:13.597
Okay, Jesus, let's go.

27:14.217 --> 27:18.163
And that's not how it works.

27:19.084 --> 27:20.786
It doesn't work in any relationship that way.

27:20.930 --> 27:27.697
You don't get the emergency wife, emergency healthy marriage, emergency best friend, no.

27:27.717 --> 27:31.041
So I turn to God, my needs, my wants, my desires.

27:31.081 --> 27:39.590
And he says, I am perfectly willing to help you navigate that, but I have to be first.

27:40.311 --> 27:49.021
You will seek me and find me when you seek me with all your heart.

27:49.041 --> 27:50.162
As I prayed about it,

27:50.530 --> 27:52.011
Because again, I don't know your circumstances.

27:53.273 --> 27:57.977
I think what God was placing in my heart, reminding me of first and then for me to share with you.

27:57.997 --> 28:01.541
I said, the invitation for you today is simple.

28:02.021 --> 28:06.465
Are you ready to turn to Him and seek Him with all your heart?

28:06.565 --> 28:08.988
You know what that looks like in your life.

28:10.089 --> 28:13.612
The Spirit is alive and well in you, and He knows what He's highlighting.

28:13.732 --> 28:14.913
You know what that means.

28:18.337 --> 28:19.858
Are you ready to pursue Him

28:20.322 --> 28:24.246
First, and entrust all these needs, wants and desires to Him.

28:24.286 --> 28:31.855
Or are you going to depend on your own self-sufficiency or on other means to address those?

28:31.875 --> 28:36.439
Because you can't wait or trust God's timing and sovereignty.

28:41.645 --> 28:42.106
He's there.

28:43.727 --> 28:44.949
He's always there.

28:45.229 --> 28:46.130
He's waiting.

28:46.370 --> 28:56.400
waiting to forgive if you've wandered off, waiting to restore if you don't feel as close, waiting to sustain if it feels too hard, waiting to guide you if you don't know where to go.

28:58.703 --> 29:02.086
All we have to do is take those steps toward him.

29:04.249 --> 29:11.697
Throughout the history of God's people, the Shema has been a central piece of God's people's identity.

29:12.137 --> 29:13.138
That is because

29:13.282 --> 29:19.668
It gives them the framework as to how God's people should live with that as the litmus test.

29:21.490 --> 29:31.881
The Shema found the different places but in Deuteronomy chapter six, four or five reads, here O Israel, the Lord our God, the Lord is one.

29:32.882 --> 29:38.528
Love the Lord your God with all your heart, with all your soul, and with all your strength.

29:39.709 --> 29:41.010
If that sounds familiar,

29:41.346 --> 29:57.141
Of course it does, it's because when Jesus was asked what the most important commandment was, out of all the hundreds of commandments, Jesus answered with the Shema, love the Lord your God with all your heart, with all your soul, and with all your strength.

29:57.161 --> 30:00.264
And then he added, love your neighbor as yourself.

30:01.465 --> 30:08.051
He basically says that the whole life of the kingdom of God, all the commandments, all the prophets, all rest on those two key pillars.

30:08.612 --> 30:10.994
Love God, love others.

30:11.330 --> 30:24.923
how interesting that in Israel's time of exile and difficulty, faithfully living for God and waiting on him, relied on them loving God and loving others by seeking the prosperity of the city.

30:29.167 --> 30:40.338
My prayer for you and for me is that we would be a people that are willing to regularly turn to the Lord with all that we have, with all that we want and all that we need.

30:42.018 --> 30:49.668
and allow Him to be in the throne of our hearts as we place those things at the foot of His throne, at the foot of the cross.

30:51.510 --> 30:53.172
And guys, this is the beauty of our God.

30:54.594 --> 30:57.438
He can handle our wants and desires.

30:58.719 --> 31:01.483
You can go to God and go, I don't want this.

31:02.464 --> 31:03.686
I don't like this job.

31:04.006 --> 31:05.088
I don't like this city.

31:05.128 --> 31:06.930
We can bring that to Him.

31:07.522 --> 31:09.804
We can actually say, he says he's a good father.

31:10.004 --> 31:11.926
We can tell him, this is what I would want.

31:12.167 --> 31:15.790
But the problem is that too often that's where the conversation stops.

31:17.672 --> 31:19.594
Hey Santa, Jesus, here's my list.

31:20.255 --> 31:20.875
This is what I want.

31:21.916 --> 31:24.198
I didn't say that first service, so you got that one.

31:26.921 --> 31:28.483
But that's not what he's calling us to.

31:28.683 --> 31:30.024
That's not how even how this works.

31:31.325 --> 31:36.050
I know we have permission to do that with God because if Jesus did it, we can do it.

31:36.514 --> 31:44.181
And we're told that Jesus in the garden looked up at his phone and said, if there's any way that this cup can be passed from me, could we do that?

31:47.124 --> 31:49.086
But the next part is the part that's hard.

31:50.687 --> 31:54.591
It's taking that want, that need, that desire.

31:54.691 --> 32:02.058
It's taking your circumstances and all that's hard about them and taking them to God and going, I need help.

32:03.119 --> 32:05.001
And this is how I want the help.

32:05.021 --> 32:06.482
And this is when I want the help.

32:06.850 --> 32:10.876
but then ultimately going, but you are God, I am not.

32:11.997 --> 32:14.921
You conquered sin and death, I did not.

32:15.362 --> 32:18.406
You tell me you love me and I can believe that.

32:18.726 --> 32:22.351
You tell me you have plans for me, plans to prosper me and not harm me.

32:22.552 --> 32:23.633
So I'll believe in that.

32:23.693 --> 32:27.799
So therefore not my will, but yours be done.

32:30.422 --> 32:35.890
Are we a people that are willing to very humbly and very honestly

32:36.322 --> 32:55.151
Take our wants and desires to the throne room of God, making him first above everything else, and letting him guide us through until the things we need and desire are answered in his way, in his time.

32:55.872 --> 33:05.266
Will we remain faithful in the waiting and trust that he is who he says he is, a good and loving God?

